olive oil
1 potato
1 white turnip
1 portion cauliflower
1 stalk celery
2 clove garlic
20 g butter
1 packet beef mince
1 sachet Herb & Mushroom Seasoning
1 packet tomato paste
1 tsp plain flour
1 sachet beef-style stock powder
¾ cup water

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Bring a medium saucepan of salted water to the boil.
• Peel potato and cut into large chunks. Peel white turnip and cut into bite-sized chunks. Chop cauliflower into small florets (including stalk!). Finely chop celery and garlic.
• Place cauliflower in a baking dish. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Roast until tender and brown around edges, 20-25 minutes.

• Cook potato and turnip in the boiling water until easily pierced with a fork, 15-18 minutes.
• Drain and return veggies to pan.
• Add the butter and a good pinch of salt. Mash until smooth. Cover to keep warm.

TIP: Save time and get more fibre by leaving the potato unpeeled!
Little cooks: Get those muscles working and help mash the potatoes!

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook beef mince and celery, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.

TIP: For best results, drain the oil from the pan before cooking the sauce.

• Reduce heat to medium, then add garlic, herb & mushroom seasoning, tomato paste and the plain flour and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add beef-style stock powder and the water and cook, stirring until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.

TIP: Add a dash more water if the mince is dry!

• Preheat grill to high. Transfer beef filling to the baking dish with cauliflower and spread turnip potato mash over the top.
• Grill until lightly golden, 10-15 minutes.

Little cooks: Join in on the fun by smoothing the mash mixture evenly over the pie!

• Divide beef and cauliflower pie between plates. Enjoy!